==English==
[[Image:HMS Royal Oak (08).jpg|thumb|right|A battleship.]]

===Etymology===
{{compound|en|battle|ship}}; shortened from ''[[line]]-of-[[battle]] [[ship]]'', attested 1794.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|military}} Large [[capital]] [[warship]] displacing tens of thousands of tons, [[heavily]] [[armoured]] and [[arm]]ed with big [[gun]]s. Battleships are now [[obsolescent]], replaced by smaller [[vessel]]s with [[guided missile]]s. Types: [[dreadnought]], [[pre-dreadnought]].
# Non-functional [[rocket]] [[stage]], used for configuration and integration tests.
# A [[guessing game]] played on [[grid paper]], see {{w|Battleship (game)}}

====Derived terms====
