===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# To [[deliberately]] [[kill]] (a person or persons).
#: ''The woman found dead in her kitchen was '''murdered''' by her husband.''
# {{lb|en|transitive|sports|figuratively|colloquial}} To [[defeat]] [[decisive]]ly.
#: ''Our team is going to '''murder''' them.''
# To [[botch]] or [[mangle]].
#* {{quote-book|1892|William Shepard Walsh|Handy-book of Literary Curiosities|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=1zo4AAAAMAAJ|page=293
|passage=Dr. Caius, the Frenchman in the play, and Evans the Welshman, "Gallia et Guallia," succeed pretty well in their efforts to '''murder''' the language.}}
# {{lb|en|figuratively|colloquial}} To [[kick ass|kick someone's ass]] or [[chew out|chew someone out]] (used to express one‚Äôs anger at somebody).
#: ''He's torn my best shirt. When I see him, I'll '''murder''' him!''
# {{lb|en|figuratively|colloquial|British}} to [[devour]], [[ravish]].
#: ''I could '''murder''' a [[hamburger]] right now.''

