===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A light of dazzling brilliancy.
# {{lb|en|figurative}} Showy brilliance that may stop a person from thinking clearly.
# {{lb|en|uncommon}} A [[herd]] of zebra.
#* '''1958''', Laurens Van der Post, ''The lost world of the Kalahari: with the great and the little memory'' ('''1998''' David Coulson edition):
#*: We were trying to stalk a '''dazzle''' of zebra which flashed in and out of a long strip of green and yellow fever trees, with an ostrich, its feathers flared like a ballet skirt around its dancing legs, on their flank, when suddenly {{...}}
#* {{quote-text|year=2009|author=Darren Paul Shearer|title=In You God Trusts|page=176|passage=Zebras move in herds which are known as "dazzles." When a lion approaches a '''dazzle''' of zebras during its hunt, {{...}}}}
#* {{quote-text|year=2010|author=Douglas Rogers|title=The Last Resort: A Memoir of Mischief and Mayhem on a Family Farm in Africa|page=22|passage=I reached the lodge as a '''dazzle''' of zebras trotted across the dirt road into thorny scrub by the game fence, and a lone kudu gazed up at me from the short grass near the swimming pool.}}

